WEBVTT

00:42.542 --> 00:45.962
SOLD OUT ON YOU

01:05.148 --> 01:07.692
Ms. Dam, what are you doing?
Didn't you hear the car?

01:21.873 --> 01:22.707
Are you okay?

01:24.501 --> 01:27.837
Ms. Dam, are you drunk?

01:38.640 --> 01:39.974
Ms. Dam.

02:08.711 --> 02:10.088
Stay here for a moment.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.142
Thank you.

05:21.612 --> 05:22.613
Ms. Dam…

05:40.882 --> 05:41.716
Mr. Mechoori?

05:48.848 --> 05:49.766
What are you…

06:09.577 --> 06:10.536
I like it.

06:17.085 --> 06:19.337
What cologne do you use?

06:19.837 --> 06:22.173
What do you think you're doing?

06:27.095 --> 06:30.056
That subtle yet nonchalant scent
of woody musk…

06:31.849 --> 06:35.311
I think our customers
would really love this.

06:37.021 --> 06:38.189
I'm not using any cologne.

06:44.904 --> 06:46.489
You want it just for yourself?

06:51.494 --> 06:52.578
You're such a jerk.

06:56.249 --> 06:57.583
You little…

06:57.667 --> 06:58.668
Ms. Dam…

09:06.504 --> 09:08.256
I'm all out.

09:17.848 --> 09:19.058
When did I scratch my foot?

09:21.018 --> 09:22.144
That hurts.

10:19.702 --> 10:20.911
Mom.

10:22.496 --> 10:24.206
Pick up.

10:25.374 --> 10:26.876
Please pick up.

11:18.928 --> 11:19.762
Hey, Mechoori!

11:22.515 --> 11:23.766
Hey, Som-yi.

11:23.849 --> 11:26.602
Shouldn't you be going to school now?
Is something wrong?

11:26.685 --> 11:28.229
Well,

11:28.312 --> 11:30.064
it's not that…

11:31.816 --> 11:32.817
Do you have any money?

11:34.402 --> 11:35.277
How much do you need?

11:35.361 --> 11:39.323
Jin-yi said she'd give me 50,000 won
if I help clean the shop next week.

11:40.491 --> 11:41.826
You want me to lend you 50,000?

11:41.909 --> 11:44.036
What are you going to use it for?

11:44.120 --> 11:44.954
"Poca"!

11:47.832 --> 11:48.749
What did you just say?

11:51.627 --> 11:53.337
Poker? You…

11:54.964 --> 11:56.173
I can't let you do that.

11:56.257 --> 11:57.716
Why not? That's my joy in life.

11:57.800 --> 11:58.926
Som-yi!

11:59.677 --> 12:02.430
Look, there are a lot
of good and fun hobbies to do.

12:02.513 --> 12:04.557
If you get addicted,
it'll be hard to quit.

12:05.141 --> 12:06.767
In any case, I can't let you gamble.

12:08.060 --> 12:08.978
What are you on about?

12:12.064 --> 12:13.357
I meant photo cards.

12:13.441 --> 12:15.234
I'm going to buy photo cards.

12:15.317 --> 12:16.610
Photo cards?

12:20.531 --> 12:21.365
Photo cards?

12:23.033 --> 12:24.034
You want 50,000 won?

12:26.495 --> 12:27.329
Mechoori.

12:27.413 --> 12:29.081
Instead of working today,

12:29.165 --> 12:31.459
why don't you go online
and study the outside world?

12:32.376 --> 12:33.544
DAM YE-JIN

12:37.339 --> 12:39.425
Mechoori, are you "stanning" her?

12:39.508 --> 12:40.468
No.

12:41.343 --> 12:42.553
What's "stanning"?

12:42.636 --> 12:43.637
Do you like her?

12:43.721 --> 12:45.097
No!

12:46.307 --> 12:49.185
I mean, something about her
was just bothering me a bit.

12:50.269 --> 12:52.354
That's how stanning starts.

12:53.814 --> 12:55.524
You want something to eat, Som-yi?

13:07.536 --> 13:08.370
Damn it.

13:08.454 --> 13:11.040
-This is bad news for Jin-yi.
-What?

13:12.625 --> 13:13.751
It's nothing.

13:14.668 --> 13:16.086
She seems fine this morning though.

13:17.755 --> 13:18.839
How would you know?

13:18.923 --> 13:20.049
She's doing a live now.

13:20.132 --> 13:21.091
A "live"?

13:21.175 --> 13:22.593
A live broadcast!

13:22.676 --> 13:25.137
Hello. Good morning.

13:25.721 --> 13:26.555
Everyone.

13:27.640 --> 13:29.892
Look at the sky. Isn't it beautiful?

13:29.975 --> 13:33.521
This is my favorite spot
by the Hangang River.

13:33.604 --> 13:35.898
I feel so refreshed when I come here.

13:36.398 --> 13:38.776
I started a live
so you all could see this too.

13:38.859 --> 13:42.655
But it doesn't even look
half as good on camera.

13:43.405 --> 13:45.824
The weather? It's already hot.

13:45.908 --> 13:49.703
Are you curious whether she slept well

13:50.454 --> 13:51.997
or if she made sure to eat her meals?

13:52.540 --> 13:54.166
I told you it's not like that.

13:54.667 --> 13:56.502
Come on, Uncle Mechoori.

14:01.674 --> 14:05.844
Was there a mistake with the last fitting?
It's so tight around the waist.

14:06.345 --> 14:08.180
We didn't change anything.

14:10.349 --> 14:11.934
Have you gained weight?

14:12.017 --> 14:13.269
Come on.

14:13.811 --> 14:16.564
You know I stay on a strict diet
before my shows.

14:17.731 --> 14:18.941
Why is this so tight?

14:22.778 --> 14:24.238
It's not much, but eat up.

14:26.407 --> 14:28.659
Here are the potatoes you like.
I grew these myself.

14:28.742 --> 14:31.328
Have some sikhye to help it go down nice.

14:36.917 --> 14:38.544
But I only had a bite of each dish…

14:38.627 --> 14:39.587
It's only on Saturdays.

14:39.670 --> 14:40.796
-Seriously.
-No way.

14:40.880 --> 14:43.090
-I mean it!
-You're starting to get on my nerves!

14:43.173 --> 14:44.633
Nice outfit today.

14:46.719 --> 14:48.345
Is it a bit small?

14:50.264 --> 14:51.181
No, it isn't.

14:52.308 --> 14:55.144
I'd like to change to heels
that cover my feet.

14:56.228 --> 14:57.855
-Let's see…
-What happened to your feet?

14:57.938 --> 14:58.939
Did you hurt yourself?

14:59.899 --> 15:02.818
I don't know. I woke up like this.
I guess I scratched them somewhere.

15:02.902 --> 15:05.362
How would that happen in your sleep?
You sure you're okay?

15:05.446 --> 15:08.365
I'm actually doing very well these days,
so don't worry.

15:09.116 --> 15:11.660
But what were you chatting about?
You sounded so excited.

15:11.744 --> 15:12.620
Well…

15:13.495 --> 15:14.622
Ms. Dam!

15:14.705 --> 15:15.998
Geez.

15:16.081 --> 15:17.124
What? What is it?

15:17.207 --> 15:19.126
We have news, and it's big news.

15:19.209 --> 15:23.297
We asked for as much storage as possible
for L'Étoile's essence,

15:23.380 --> 15:26.300
and they actually emptied out
an entire warehouse for us!

15:26.383 --> 15:28.344
An entire warehouse?

15:28.427 --> 15:30.638
Just thinking of filling
that warehouse with essence

15:30.721 --> 15:32.348
is giving me a dopamine rush!

15:32.431 --> 15:33.474
A huge rush!

15:33.557 --> 15:35.851
You might just set a new record

15:35.935 --> 15:37.811
for the highest sales
in the shortest time!

15:37.895 --> 15:39.271
A new record!

15:39.939 --> 15:42.358
Are talks going smoothly
with Gojeuneok Bio?

15:42.441 --> 15:43.943
Why would you even ask that?

15:44.026 --> 15:45.152
Don't you know Ye-jin?

15:45.235 --> 15:47.738
Tell Mr. Seo to gather
all the essence they can provide.

15:47.821 --> 15:49.073
And you'll sell all of them.

15:49.156 --> 15:50.282
Yes, everything.

16:06.215 --> 16:08.008
AN ENTIRE WAREHOUSE EMPTIED OUT

16:13.055 --> 16:14.348
Mr. Mechoori!

16:14.431 --> 16:16.266
No. I mean, Mr. Matthew Lee!

16:16.350 --> 16:18.519
I'm in huge trouble. Please help me out.

16:19.311 --> 16:22.314
Mr. Lee! Please help me!

16:22.398 --> 16:24.858
I swear I won't ask for a favor
like this again! Please!

16:24.942 --> 16:26.986
If you help me out just this once…

16:32.282 --> 16:33.867
GO BACK. THERE ARE NO MUSHROOMS

16:35.452 --> 16:37.037
Mechoori… I mean, Mr. Matthew Lee.

16:37.121 --> 16:39.748
Sir, please help me out just this once!

16:39.832 --> 16:41.333
NO. LEAVE

16:41.417 --> 16:43.127
GO AWAY

16:43.210 --> 16:45.045
YOU WEREN'T CONSIDERATE OF ME

16:46.296 --> 16:48.340
THESE ARE THE CONSEQUENCES

16:48.424 --> 16:49.425
Those wings are gross!

16:49.508 --> 16:51.301
No, I didn't mean that. I'm sorry.

16:51.385 --> 16:53.554
I'm sorry. I take that back.
Please forgive me!

16:55.472 --> 16:57.099
DARN IT

16:58.851 --> 17:00.185
YOU WON'T EVEN SEE THE MUSHROOMS

17:00.269 --> 17:02.187
LET ME BE CLEAR

17:02.271 --> 17:06.025
YOU'LL NEVER BE ABLE TO SEE
MY MUSHROOMS AGAIN

17:06.108 --> 17:08.318
GOODBYE!

17:08.402 --> 17:10.946
Mr. Lee, please come back! Don't leave!

17:11.822 --> 17:13.407
Right! I'm Dam Ye-jin.

17:13.490 --> 17:16.702
Of course! Don't worry,
and secure as much stock as you can!

17:16.785 --> 17:19.621
Get as much as you want!
We'll support you all the way. Got that?

17:21.915 --> 17:24.585
You two are so reliable.

17:27.046 --> 17:28.338
I have an urgent meeting.

17:36.305 --> 17:40.017
Granny, what do we do about Jin-yi now?

17:40.642 --> 17:42.478
She's going to lose Mechoori
to someone else.

17:43.228 --> 17:45.230
Why? What's wrong with Jin-yi?

17:45.314 --> 17:48.442
My sister has no chance against her.

17:48.525 --> 17:50.611
What's on the inside matters more.

17:51.278 --> 17:55.157
Then, who do you think is prettier?
Jin-yi or Dam Ye-jin?

17:56.366 --> 17:57.659
-Jin.
-What?

17:58.410 --> 18:00.079
Dam Ye-jin.

18:00.162 --> 18:02.664
She does have a bright and lovely smile.

18:02.748 --> 18:03.832
Granny!

18:09.588 --> 18:10.964
Hey, sweetie.

18:11.715 --> 18:13.008
-Mechoori?
-Mechoori?

18:14.259 --> 18:16.720
Why are you asking about Mechoori?
Who are you?

18:16.804 --> 18:18.222
Me? I'm Dam Ye-jin.

18:18.305 --> 18:19.389
Who are you?

18:21.975 --> 18:23.477
None of your business.

18:23.560 --> 18:26.855
Hey. Are you close with our Mechoori?

18:26.939 --> 18:29.399
"Our Mechoori"? Are you two close?

18:29.483 --> 18:31.318
Yes, we're very close!

18:32.611 --> 18:33.487
Really?

18:33.570 --> 18:35.906
Then, I guess you'll know
where he is right now.

18:36.532 --> 18:37.825
Why do you want to know?

18:37.908 --> 18:39.868
Because I'm on my way to see him.

18:39.952 --> 18:42.412
He's busy harvesting corn today.

18:42.496 --> 18:44.498
Corn? When? What time?

18:45.749 --> 18:48.585
Wait. You might not know that
even if you're close.

18:48.669 --> 18:49.586
Come on.

18:50.170 --> 18:53.215
I know Mechoori's entire schedule, okay?

18:53.799 --> 18:56.301
Is that so?
Then, let's discuss the details later.

18:59.221 --> 19:00.055
Why did she hang up?

19:02.057 --> 19:02.891
She hung up?

19:02.975 --> 19:04.184
She just hung up.

19:04.977 --> 19:05.811
Gosh…

19:13.819 --> 19:15.237
The home shopping host, Dam Ye-jin?

19:16.113 --> 19:17.739
So that was you. Hi.

19:19.491 --> 19:22.161
Where did you buy that mask though?

19:22.244 --> 19:24.371
It looks comfortable and nice.

19:24.454 --> 19:25.414
I didn't buy this.

19:25.497 --> 19:26.498
Really?

19:29.042 --> 19:31.044
But shouldn't you be in school
at this hour?

19:31.753 --> 19:34.464
I'm receiving life lessons from Granny.

19:34.548 --> 19:36.466
I'm earning experience from an elder.

19:37.801 --> 19:39.428
Then, how about this kind of experience?

19:41.096 --> 19:43.015
Let's begin our warmup. All right.

19:44.349 --> 19:47.352
National exercise, start!

19:47.436 --> 19:48.937
Okay, hurry on in here!

19:49.021 --> 19:50.689
One, two, three,

19:50.772 --> 19:53.984
four, five, six, seven, eight…

19:54.067 --> 19:55.569
Look at that!

19:55.652 --> 19:57.905
Two, three, four, five, six.

19:57.988 --> 20:00.490
You can look later. Come on and do this!

20:01.283 --> 20:02.784
Okay, the knees!

20:02.868 --> 20:06.747
Three, four, five, six, seven, eight.

20:06.830 --> 20:13.128
Two, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, and arms!

20:13.212 --> 20:16.924
One, two, three, four, five, six…

20:17.424 --> 20:18.842
Som-yi, what about school?

20:19.551 --> 20:20.385
What?

20:21.178 --> 20:22.012
What is this?

20:22.596 --> 20:23.430
Oh, right!

20:24.765 --> 20:28.143
It's been a long time, Mr. Lee.

20:28.227 --> 20:29.561
Goodness…

20:29.645 --> 20:30.854
Gracious.

20:33.023 --> 20:34.066
It's not what you think.

20:34.149 --> 20:36.610
I promise I'm not here
to pester you today.

20:38.237 --> 20:41.490
Ms. Yang said she's harvesting corn,
so I came to help out.

20:42.616 --> 20:43.867
Help harvest corn?

20:43.951 --> 20:45.911
Yes. I'm actually very good with my hands.

20:45.994 --> 20:48.080
It's fine. We have enough people.

20:48.163 --> 20:49.122
Come on.

20:49.623 --> 20:51.959
I bet you'll like it
when you see me working.

20:53.126 --> 20:55.963
You'll like it.

20:56.046 --> 20:57.464
I like it.

21:00.133 --> 21:01.635
Are you all right?

21:02.511 --> 21:05.847
Mr. Lee, you should take good care
of your health when you're busy.

21:06.431 --> 21:09.851
Don't worry about me.
You should be taking care of yourself.

21:10.602 --> 21:11.520
What?

21:11.603 --> 21:13.146
I mean…

21:13.230 --> 21:15.440
Mechoori! We're all waiting!

21:15.524 --> 21:16.358
Goodness.

21:17.192 --> 21:21.071
Okay, everyone! If you're ready,
let's start heading to the field!

21:21.154 --> 21:22.364
What's with him?

21:23.991 --> 21:25.367
Wait for me!

21:25.909 --> 21:27.828
HARVEST BEGINS

21:27.911 --> 21:32.207
It has nothing to do with you

21:32.291 --> 21:37.379
You never existed from the start

21:40.507 --> 21:45.137
Gosh, please do your best to harvest these
for my son-in-law's makgeolli!

21:45.220 --> 21:46.847
-Sure!
-Of course!

21:46.930 --> 21:48.765
Don't worry about it!

21:48.849 --> 21:52.269
My son-in-law's makgeolli business
is going to be a huge success.

21:52.352 --> 21:54.271
The makgeolli will be a big hit!

21:54.938 --> 21:55.981
-A big hit!
-It'll be big!

21:57.274 --> 21:59.484
The makgeolli will be a big hit!

22:01.653 --> 22:02.863
There we go.

22:06.033 --> 22:08.076
This one's huge.

22:18.003 --> 22:19.254
It's so hot.

22:20.213 --> 22:21.131
This is exhausting.

22:21.214 --> 22:22.549
DEOKPUNG CORNFIELD
SUPER SWEET CORN

22:22.632 --> 22:25.677
I feel like I'm going to melt.

22:27.679 --> 22:28.889
I can't do this anymore.

22:29.431 --> 22:31.308
I can't. This is killing me.

22:31.892 --> 22:33.226
I'm so exhausted.

22:50.243 --> 22:51.161
I can do it.

22:52.120 --> 22:52.996
It's doable.

22:53.830 --> 22:54.831
I can do it.

23:14.935 --> 23:16.520
It's time for some snacks.

23:16.603 --> 23:19.272
-Let's go have some snacks.
-Is it time already?

23:19.356 --> 23:20.941
Let's go have snacks.

23:23.777 --> 23:25.153
Eat up, everyone!

23:25.237 --> 23:27.280
Let's eat!

23:28.782 --> 23:30.867
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

23:36.081 --> 23:37.541
They're all carbs.

23:39.084 --> 23:40.001
This is so refreshing.

23:40.085 --> 23:41.837
Sweetie, aren't you eating?

23:41.920 --> 23:44.631
No, ma'am. I have to lose weight.

23:44.714 --> 23:47.509
You eat snacks to keep your energy up.

23:47.592 --> 23:50.095
It's fine.
I usually don't eat much anyway.

23:50.178 --> 23:52.264
Come on. Have a bite.

23:52.347 --> 23:53.807
-It's really fine--
-Just one.

23:55.600 --> 23:57.102
Ma'am!

23:57.185 --> 23:59.479
It's okay.
Delicious food doesn't count. Eat up.

23:59.563 --> 24:00.814
You'll be fine.

24:05.193 --> 24:06.111
Eat up.

24:18.623 --> 24:19.708
It's so good!

24:19.791 --> 24:20.625
DELICIOUS

24:32.596 --> 24:34.097
That was so good!

24:34.931 --> 24:38.810
A refreshing iced Americano
would wash it all down perfectly, right?

24:38.894 --> 24:40.020
Right…

24:40.103 --> 24:42.522
Have some iced coffee, everyone!

24:43.064 --> 24:44.191
Jin-yi!

24:44.274 --> 24:45.609
Hi!

24:46.193 --> 24:47.402
Who is she?

24:47.485 --> 24:49.070
She's the face of Deokpung.

24:49.154 --> 24:51.031
We wouldn't be able to live without her.

24:51.114 --> 24:53.450
This, this, and this.

24:53.533 --> 24:55.118
I bought all these from her shop.

24:55.202 --> 24:56.620
-These too.
-These too.

24:59.998 --> 25:00.832
All right.

25:03.418 --> 25:04.336
Ta-da.

25:05.587 --> 25:07.005
That's refreshing!

25:07.088 --> 25:08.423
Everyone, take one!

25:09.591 --> 25:10.926
It's iced coffee.

25:11.009 --> 25:12.969
She's my sister. Isn't she pretty?

25:13.053 --> 25:14.971
She's got a great personality too.

25:15.055 --> 25:16.723
Som-yi! What are you doing here?

25:17.933 --> 25:19.434
I'll take back that last part.

25:20.143 --> 25:21.436
You little…

25:21.519 --> 25:22.354
Ae-ra.

25:23.730 --> 25:25.232
Would you like to join me?

25:27.817 --> 25:28.902
How cute.

25:30.195 --> 25:31.529
She's always rejecting me.

25:31.613 --> 25:32.906
Are you still trying to woo her?

25:32.989 --> 25:34.741
I wouldn't accept you
if I were her either.

25:37.118 --> 25:39.537
You know we're harvesting
the super sweet corn today.

25:39.621 --> 25:41.539
I told you I wouldn't buy them
for that price.

25:41.623 --> 25:43.416
I can't give them to you
for half the price.

25:43.500 --> 25:44.334
Then…

25:44.417 --> 25:45.710
I have nothing more to say.

25:45.794 --> 25:48.421
I even refused offers
from department stores

25:48.505 --> 25:50.423
to provide them
for your makgeolli factory.

25:50.507 --> 25:52.050
You can't just suddenly do this.

25:53.134 --> 25:54.886
Then, we'll take the penalty fees

25:54.970 --> 25:57.097
and terminate our business
with your factory.

26:00.100 --> 26:01.017
Mechoori.

26:02.310 --> 26:03.937
Sir, please don't…

26:04.020 --> 26:05.480
Can't you let this slide?

26:06.231 --> 26:08.358
My sales are declining,

26:08.441 --> 26:10.360
and my staff are quitting one by one.

26:12.487 --> 26:15.448
I'm even doing deliveries myself now!

26:15.949 --> 26:17.242
To be honest,

26:17.325 --> 26:19.411
I asked for half price
and expected you to refuse.

26:22.497 --> 26:25.709
Does your mother-in-law know
the business isn't doing well?

26:26.293 --> 26:29.045
Please keep this a secret from her.

26:32.048 --> 26:35.468
My son-in-law said he won't buy the corn?

26:35.552 --> 26:39.347
Yes. He's developing a new product,
so we'll have to sell them somewhere else.

26:39.431 --> 26:41.224
Why refuse such good-quality corn?

26:41.308 --> 26:42.976
What about all this corn then?

26:44.644 --> 26:47.397
It'll be fine.
I'll find another way to deal with them.

26:47.480 --> 26:49.274
Let's end work here today.

26:49.357 --> 26:50.984
Thank you, everyone.

26:51.067 --> 26:52.569
They won't taste good at all

26:52.652 --> 26:55.822
if they're not picked
within the next two days.

26:55.905 --> 26:57.032
Right.

26:57.115 --> 26:58.658
Oh, dear.

26:58.742 --> 27:00.994
Ma'am, I'll take you home.

27:01.077 --> 27:03.121
Forget it! I'll pick them all before I go.

27:04.539 --> 27:05.498
Ma'am…

27:05.582 --> 27:07.083
There's nowhere to store them anyway,

27:07.167 --> 27:08.877
and it's better
to keep them on the stalks.

27:08.960 --> 27:11.463
So go and get some rest today.
I'll think about what to do.

27:36.446 --> 27:37.530
So…

27:37.614 --> 27:41.034
all this corn might go to waste.

27:42.369 --> 27:44.204
You should head back too.

27:44.913 --> 27:46.081
Thanks for helping.

27:46.164 --> 27:48.666
I want to help find a solution.

27:48.750 --> 27:51.586
It's fine. I can find another client.

27:51.669 --> 27:53.505
With fresh produce, time is everything.

27:53.588 --> 27:55.507
They're drying out even as we speak.

27:55.590 --> 27:57.384
This has nothing to do with you.

27:58.885 --> 28:01.805
I helped pick these as I suffered
in the scorching sun too.

28:01.888 --> 28:03.723
But they're about to go to waste.

28:03.807 --> 28:05.809
How can I just leave?
Everyone worked so hard.

28:06.643 --> 28:07.894
I can't just go.

28:14.317 --> 28:15.151
Let's sell them.

28:16.277 --> 28:17.112
What?

28:17.195 --> 28:20.031
Let's sell them through a livestream.

28:21.616 --> 28:22.742
Why would you do that?

28:22.826 --> 28:24.869
My nickname is Live Info Show.

28:24.953 --> 28:26.621
I host with life info from the field.

28:26.704 --> 28:27.539
So?

28:27.622 --> 28:28.748
"So?"

28:29.666 --> 28:32.210
You might not realize what this means,

28:32.293 --> 28:34.045
but this is an incredible offer.

28:38.133 --> 28:40.260
Are you not confident about their quality?

28:43.388 --> 28:45.890
The corn here averages 20 Brix.

28:45.974 --> 28:47.100
Do you know what that means?

28:47.183 --> 28:49.102
They're as sweet as top-quality apples,

28:49.185 --> 28:52.188
so they're 100 times more prone
to pests than regular corn,

28:52.272 --> 28:54.107
but we only used natural fertilizer.

28:55.024 --> 28:58.403
Yes. That's why I made such a big decision
as Korea's top home shopping host.

28:59.154 --> 29:00.905
Gather all the elders again.

29:05.660 --> 29:06.619
Hey, Mr. Hwang.

29:06.703 --> 29:08.997
Can you give me the number
of the online department head?

29:10.081 --> 29:12.167
-Where do you want this?
-I'll check for you!

29:12.959 --> 29:14.210
Yes, right there.

29:14.294 --> 29:18.256
FRESH AND STEAMED SUPER SWEET CORN
NATIONWIDE DELIVERY AVAILABLE

29:19.466 --> 29:21.468
DAM YE-JIN'S FIRST
LIVESTREAM SHOPPING BROADCAST

29:24.804 --> 29:26.389
You two stay in the field,

29:26.473 --> 29:30.101
and when the camera comes in,
pick a nice, plump one and bite into it.

29:31.936 --> 29:34.397
Ma'am, you can cook
anything you want with the corn here.

29:34.481 --> 29:35.440
All right.

29:35.523 --> 29:36.858
-Okay!
-Okay!

29:40.320 --> 29:41.780
Our talented director.

29:41.863 --> 29:44.324
Zoom right in on me
when I'm trying the corn later.

29:44.407 --> 29:48.077
I won't lose you even if you
suddenly run off, so do whatever you want!

29:51.372 --> 29:53.625
I found a warehouse
that can handle up to 3,000 boxes.

29:54.375 --> 29:55.335
Three thousand boxes…

29:55.418 --> 29:57.170
Okay! I'll sell them all in ten minutes.

29:57.253 --> 29:58.129
Hang on.

29:58.213 --> 30:01.174
Ms. Dam, are you going to do
the live in that outfit?

30:01.758 --> 30:03.426
This will be aired nationwide.

30:04.511 --> 30:07.138
What other outfit
could be better for selling corn?

30:07.222 --> 30:09.057
Well, it's fine with me.

30:12.227 --> 30:14.270
I'm refreshing the page.

30:14.354 --> 30:15.814
LIMITED OFFER FOR JUST TODAY!

30:16.981 --> 30:17.899
Look at that!

30:19.067 --> 30:20.360
We did it!

30:20.443 --> 30:22.070
We can do the live now!

30:27.200 --> 30:28.868
-There's ten minutes left.
-Right.

30:29.619 --> 30:30.453
Let's go.

30:34.082 --> 30:36.084
DEOKPUNG COMMUNITY CENTER

30:38.545 --> 30:39.838
Come on, hurry.

30:39.921 --> 30:41.297
We don't have time.

30:48.721 --> 30:49.722
What is this?

30:50.390 --> 30:52.016
You didn't know either, did you?

30:53.810 --> 30:56.437
You ran in here to tell me this?
Were you excited to tattle?

30:56.521 --> 30:59.232
Just yesterday, she was desperate
about keeping her time slot.

30:59.315 --> 31:01.943
But now, she's suddenly doing
a livestream shopping broadcast.

31:02.026 --> 31:03.611
She's selling corn.

31:05.405 --> 31:08.616
She caught up with you
even after that incident five years ago.

31:09.242 --> 31:10.159
Ms. Dong.

31:10.952 --> 31:13.288
Dam Ye-jin is the face of HIT.

31:14.038 --> 31:16.040
This affects HIT's image.

31:16.916 --> 31:17.834
Image?

31:18.835 --> 31:21.629
She's selling high-quality products
at a reasonable price.

31:21.713 --> 31:24.924
I think she's maintaining our image
properly as a home shopping host.

31:25.008 --> 31:27.760
You're just going to let her
do whatever she pleases?

31:27.844 --> 31:28.803
All I'm looking for

31:29.762 --> 31:30.680
is survival.

31:32.140 --> 31:33.057
Yun-ji.

31:33.141 --> 31:35.351
Stop acting all high and mighty

31:36.269 --> 31:38.187
and think about how to survive.

31:38.938 --> 31:41.858
Hello, everyone.
I'm home shopping host Dam Ye-jin.

31:41.941 --> 31:44.444
You must be wondering what I'm doing here.

31:44.527 --> 31:46.529
Starting now, for 30 minutes…

31:47.322 --> 31:51.910
For just 30 minutes, I'm going to offer
super sweet corn from Deokpung Village.

31:51.993 --> 31:55.747
With ten ears of corn per box,
there's a total of 3,000 boxes.

31:55.830 --> 31:58.499
This is a limited-time offer sale
for these 3,000 boxes!

31:59.334 --> 32:00.168
DEOKPUNG CORNFIELD

32:00.251 --> 32:03.129
We'll be delivering fresh corn
straight from Deokpung Village,

32:03.212 --> 32:05.006
the place where they were grown.

32:05.089 --> 32:06.174
SUPER SWEET CORN

32:06.257 --> 32:08.134
So make your orders now.

32:08.718 --> 32:11.721
I see the farmers working hard
to harvest the corn right now.

32:11.804 --> 32:13.222
How about a brief interview?

32:13.306 --> 32:14.807
Hello, sirs.

32:14.891 --> 32:16.476
-Hello.
-Hello.

32:16.559 --> 32:18.436
Can you show us the corn?

32:18.519 --> 32:19.938
The corn?

32:20.021 --> 32:21.147
All right.

32:21.814 --> 32:23.066
There we go!

32:23.149 --> 32:26.986
We didn't use any pesticides,
so you can eat it raw.

32:27.070 --> 32:29.781
I'll try to make
an acrostic poem with corn.

32:29.864 --> 32:31.532
-C!
-Completely tasty.

32:31.616 --> 32:33.034
-OR!
-Oh, right. It goes right down.

32:33.117 --> 32:35.787
-N!
-Nice… and refreshing alcohol!

32:35.870 --> 32:36.955
-Super sweet--
-You idiot.

32:37.038 --> 32:40.667
Everyone, look at how plump
these kernels are.

32:40.750 --> 32:43.586
This ear of corn is
as big as my arm, isn't it?

32:44.087 --> 32:46.297
They're delicious
even if you eat them raw,

32:46.381 --> 32:48.925
but there are a variety
of ways to enjoy them.

32:49.008 --> 32:50.343
Shall we take a look?

32:50.426 --> 32:51.427
Hello!

32:51.511 --> 32:53.137
What is this?

32:53.221 --> 32:55.765
This is a tasty corn pancake!

32:55.848 --> 32:57.684
Corn pancakes?

32:57.767 --> 32:59.769
And this is corn salad.

33:01.187 --> 33:04.649
Even if you're not a good cook,
there's no need to worry.

33:04.732 --> 33:07.193
It still tastes incredible
if you eat them raw.

33:08.945 --> 33:12.198
They're as sweet as fruit.
Let me offer our cameraman a bite too.

33:12.281 --> 33:13.199
3,000 BOXES SOLD OUT

33:15.118 --> 33:16.160
Sold out.

33:17.036 --> 33:17.996
Sold out!

33:18.079 --> 33:20.289
We sold out!

33:22.083 --> 33:26.879
Thank you for showing us so much support
despite this being an unexpected live.

33:26.963 --> 33:30.550
All right, I'll see you again
tomorrow evening on It's a HIT!

33:30.633 --> 33:32.719
Thank you for all your love today.

33:32.802 --> 33:35.388
This has been Dam Ye-jin. Thank you!

33:35.471 --> 33:36.597
Cut!

33:39.892 --> 33:41.519
We sold out!

33:41.602 --> 33:43.771
Sold out! We sold out!

33:44.731 --> 33:46.065
Ms. Yang!

33:46.149 --> 33:50.319
Thank heavens!
Thank you, God! Thank you, Buddha!

33:50.903 --> 33:53.990
You're my granddaughter now, sweetie.

33:54.073 --> 33:56.576
It's only because
the corn was such high-quality.

33:56.659 --> 33:58.703
Not because you're pretty?

33:59.495 --> 34:01.748
Come here, everyone!
Let's take a selfie together!

34:01.831 --> 34:02.957
Look here!

34:05.877 --> 34:07.170
Mechoori!

34:07.253 --> 34:10.256
We have no time.
We have to harvest 3,000 boxes of corn!

34:10.923 --> 34:12.425
-Let's get to work.
-All right.

34:12.508 --> 34:15.094
-I'll call everyone who's free.
-Me too.

34:15.178 --> 34:18.306
You don't have any friends.
Just go and start picking.

34:21.642 --> 34:22.727
Sweetie!

34:25.646 --> 34:26.564
Ms. Dam.

34:30.318 --> 34:31.402
Ms. Dam?

34:32.904 --> 34:33.821
Are you awake?

34:41.162 --> 34:42.497
Mr. Mechoori?

34:44.665 --> 34:45.833
Ms. Dam.

34:46.417 --> 34:48.503
Can you recognize me?

34:48.586 --> 34:50.755
Can you recognize me or not?

34:51.672 --> 34:53.674
Gosh, this is terrible!

34:53.758 --> 34:54.634
Ms. Dam.

34:55.885 --> 34:57.261
Ms. Dam!

34:57.345 --> 34:59.347
Are you all right?

34:59.430 --> 35:00.515
Ms. Dam!

35:00.598 --> 35:01.599
Ms. Dam…

35:03.267 --> 35:04.352
What was that?

35:07.647 --> 35:09.273
Ms. Dam. Are you all right?

35:12.068 --> 35:13.361
This is the hospital, right?

35:14.153 --> 35:16.906
Unbelievable.
This is the first time I've ever fainted.

35:16.989 --> 35:17.865
Right…

35:19.200 --> 35:23.079
Did I get carried here
like in a romance movie?

35:24.580 --> 35:25.623
Well…

35:28.042 --> 35:32.296
I thought that was all made up,
but I guess it's real.

35:32.380 --> 35:36.342
When I saw scenes like that
in romance movies,

35:37.385 --> 35:40.179
I thought they were exaggerating.

35:42.181 --> 35:43.808
But it was real.

35:46.102 --> 35:47.186
Jung-muk.

35:47.270 --> 35:49.397
I don't think
Ms. Dam is in her right mind.

35:49.480 --> 35:51.816
-This feels so familiar.
-She seems possessed.

35:52.316 --> 35:54.819
What if she's about to die?

35:54.902 --> 35:56.779
Jung-muk! Come and check!

35:56.863 --> 35:58.406
It's just heatstroke.

35:58.489 --> 36:00.116
People don't die that easily.

36:04.162 --> 36:06.038
So this is what it's like.

36:07.165 --> 36:08.666
WOORI DEOKPUNG MEDICAL CLINIC

36:08.749 --> 36:10.126
It's heatstroke.

36:10.209 --> 36:12.295
No, it was from being out in the sun.

36:13.379 --> 36:15.464
Yeah. She'll get better after some rest.

36:17.216 --> 36:20.178
But who is she? You seem so worried.

36:20.887 --> 36:22.138
It's nothing.

36:22.221 --> 36:24.098
All right. Bye.

36:32.982 --> 36:34.150
Hey, Mechoori.

36:39.655 --> 36:40.615
What is this?

36:45.786 --> 36:47.288
Why are you giving me so much?

36:47.371 --> 36:49.624
I said it was only half price
to use the warehouse.

36:49.707 --> 36:52.001
I can't accept this much.

36:52.084 --> 36:54.712
I'm giving Ms. Yang
one less thing to worry about.

36:55.379 --> 36:58.716
And your makgeolli
is like medicine for the elders here.

36:58.799 --> 37:00.218
It'd be a disaster if it was gone.

37:00.885 --> 37:02.428
And remember not to skip your meals.

37:05.431 --> 37:06.349
Mechoori.

37:06.432 --> 37:08.517
DEOKPUNG SUPER SWEET CORN
MAKGEOLLI BREWERY

37:08.601 --> 37:12.146
Gosh, our little quail is so kind.

37:12.230 --> 37:14.565
Let's go inside and sleep now. Okay.

37:15.399 --> 37:17.193
There you go. It's okay. Get some sleep.

37:18.903 --> 37:19.820
Hey, Dad.

37:20.404 --> 37:22.782
Hey. What happened?

37:22.865 --> 37:25.117
Is she okay? Is she awake? How is she?

37:25.201 --> 37:26.285
She had heatstroke.

37:26.369 --> 37:28.287
She's Mechoori's girlfriend, right?

37:28.371 --> 37:29.205
Girlfriend?

37:30.164 --> 37:31.249
What?

37:31.332 --> 37:33.417
It seems like
you're the one who got heatstroke.

37:33.918 --> 37:35.336
SALES COMMISSION AGREEMENT

37:36.087 --> 37:37.213
My goodness.

37:38.214 --> 37:40.174
I told you I don't need
any of the profits.

37:42.635 --> 37:45.388
You're receiving it fair and square,
so don't feel bad about it.

37:46.639 --> 37:47.848
You know,

37:47.932 --> 37:50.184
this is a complicated way
of saying thank you.

37:58.859 --> 38:00.194
-What?
-Aren't you leaving?

38:00.778 --> 38:02.113
I was just about to.

38:11.330 --> 38:12.540
Hang on.

38:12.623 --> 38:15.167
What's going on?
Why am I suddenly so dizzy?

38:15.251 --> 38:16.252
Just a moment.

38:19.672 --> 38:22.383
Hold on, I'm seriously not faking this.

38:23.175 --> 38:24.093
What's wrong with me?

38:25.886 --> 38:27.305
I need to lie down. Hang on.

38:29.098 --> 38:29.932
Just a moment.

38:34.270 --> 38:35.271
Are you serious?

38:35.354 --> 38:38.107
I can't even hold my head up.

38:39.567 --> 38:42.820
I have some salt and glucose tablets
in my bag over there.

38:42.903 --> 38:44.238
Could you get them for me?

38:47.158 --> 38:49.785
You can just empty out my bag.

38:49.869 --> 38:51.871
It's an emergency. I'm sorry.

38:51.954 --> 38:53.289
Why is my head spinning?

38:57.585 --> 38:58.669
Yes, I think that's it.

38:58.753 --> 38:59.837
It's that one.

39:01.339 --> 39:02.715
This is killing me.

39:06.802 --> 39:07.803
This is so strange.

39:11.474 --> 39:12.433
Gosh, my head.

39:15.186 --> 39:16.020
Get up.

39:16.687 --> 39:17.897
Gosh.

39:19.482 --> 39:20.524
Thank you.

39:27.198 --> 39:28.115
Gosh.

39:28.699 --> 39:29.575
Hang on.

39:32.828 --> 39:34.747
Why are you so set
on overworking yourself?

39:36.499 --> 39:37.625
Me?

39:37.708 --> 39:41.295
You don't treat your injuries properly
and get heatstroke after working too hard.

39:43.089 --> 39:44.006
I know, right?

39:44.882 --> 39:48.260
Who do you think is the cause of all that?

39:51.055 --> 39:54.308
Whatever you do,
nothing's going to change.

39:55.309 --> 39:56.394
So stop wasting your time.

40:00.147 --> 40:01.607
Hey, I'm sick.

40:02.733 --> 40:04.735
You're hurting me more with these truths.

40:08.447 --> 40:09.281
Hey.

40:10.116 --> 40:12.910
Let me rest a bit on your sofa.

40:12.993 --> 40:14.620
I really can't move right now.

40:15.496 --> 40:16.705
Just a second.

40:17.498 --> 40:18.791
Wait.

40:22.420 --> 40:23.504
Stay still.

40:33.931 --> 40:34.849
Why?

40:40.938 --> 40:42.022
You're crumpling up my rug.

40:54.285 --> 40:55.244
Gosh.

40:56.120 --> 40:58.205
Why is it so far away? It's killing me.

41:04.253 --> 41:05.588
I'll just rest here.

41:44.752 --> 41:46.128
Gosh, my head.

41:46.837 --> 41:49.757
I told you I have a headache.

41:51.550 --> 41:52.718
My head…

41:54.094 --> 41:55.054
Geez.

41:56.305 --> 41:57.973
He's such a weirdo.

42:39.181 --> 42:41.517
What? Hey, where's my shirt?

42:44.311 --> 42:50.109
Now, I'll just let myself

42:50.192 --> 42:53.279
Go with the flow

42:53.362 --> 42:55.614
It has nothing to do…

42:55.698 --> 42:57.449
What?

42:57.533 --> 42:58.367
What is that?

43:02.830 --> 43:04.081
No. Please.

43:07.293 --> 43:09.169
Please back up.

43:15.175 --> 43:16.260
Damn it!

43:22.016 --> 43:23.767
I'm busy.

43:25.894 --> 43:27.271
What? What is this?

43:38.991 --> 43:41.577
Sir, let me pass.

43:41.660 --> 43:43.245
Can you move your vehicle?

43:57.551 --> 43:59.303
What are you doing?

43:59.386 --> 44:00.679
I said move your car!

44:01.847 --> 44:04.224
It seems like
this is your first time here.

44:04.308 --> 44:06.685
But this is a one-way street.

44:08.479 --> 44:10.397
There's no such thing on a farm road!

44:10.481 --> 44:12.524
I've come all the way in.
I have the right of way!

44:12.608 --> 44:14.234
You know what? Forget it.

44:16.070 --> 44:18.906
This is the way out!

44:25.746 --> 44:27.373
He has a weird look.

44:27.456 --> 44:29.291
I have to back up. I should go.

44:34.213 --> 44:35.089
What was that?

44:36.548 --> 44:39.218
Damn it, it's stuck!

44:39.301 --> 44:40.761
Wait. Hold on.

44:49.978 --> 44:50.938
Come on…

44:52.064 --> 44:52.898
No.

44:52.981 --> 44:54.191
Hey, that lunatic is coming.

44:54.274 --> 44:56.402
Please, come on…

44:57.569 --> 44:59.446
Listen, I was just about to back up…

45:05.869 --> 45:07.037
Where is he going?

45:07.663 --> 45:10.666
Wait. What is he doing?

45:45.951 --> 45:47.453
I'll back up for you this time.

45:48.787 --> 45:49.872
Go on.

46:04.303 --> 46:06.638
Who the hell is this potato-looking guy?

46:06.722 --> 46:10.184
Get it together, you lunatic!
Are you crazy?

46:38.045 --> 46:39.254
What are you taking home?

46:40.380 --> 46:41.798
A car, of course.

46:41.882 --> 46:43.425
You're driving in that condition?

46:44.426 --> 46:45.594
Gosh, I'm so touched.

46:45.677 --> 46:47.304
Are you worried about me?

46:48.013 --> 46:49.473
If you feel bad,

46:49.556 --> 46:52.184
then take a look at the documents
I left on your table.

46:53.018 --> 46:53.894
Goodbye, then.

47:01.026 --> 47:03.695
What's going on? Who is that?

47:05.447 --> 47:06.823
Who is it? Who?

47:10.744 --> 47:12.663
-Let's go now.
-I won't let this slide.

47:32.224 --> 47:34.893
I can sell the essence
even better than the corn.

47:43.193 --> 47:45.070
That guy back there was him, wasn't it?

47:45.862 --> 47:47.072
From Gojeuneok whatever?

47:49.491 --> 47:51.159
I should've given him a piece of my mind.

47:51.785 --> 47:52.619
Why?

47:54.788 --> 47:57.291
He made you work until you got heatstroke.

47:57.374 --> 47:59.501
Not even dogs are trained that harshly!

47:59.585 --> 48:01.169
So he thinks he can boss you around?

48:01.253 --> 48:02.462
He's not like that.

48:07.009 --> 48:08.093
What's with you?

48:09.970 --> 48:10.846
What?

48:16.351 --> 48:18.395
Dam Ye-jin. Go in and get some rest.

48:18.478 --> 48:19.313
Okay.

48:19.396 --> 48:20.731
Don't do anything and just sleep.

48:20.814 --> 48:22.566
Okay, already. Go on.

48:22.649 --> 48:23.483
Bye.

48:23.567 --> 48:25.444
-Bye.
-Drive safe.

48:31.491 --> 48:32.367
I'm so tired.

48:36.913 --> 48:38.248
Goodness.

48:38.332 --> 48:41.793
Ye-jin, get a grip. This isn't the time.

48:44.087 --> 48:45.797
I need some caffeine in my blood.

48:50.886 --> 48:52.429
I made an order by phone.

48:52.512 --> 48:53.513
Just a moment, please.

48:53.597 --> 48:54.514
All right.

49:00.062 --> 49:01.730
-Here you go.
-Right.

49:03.649 --> 49:06.193
-Thank you.
-Thank you. Have a nice night.

49:09.237 --> 49:10.489
Thank you.

49:12.199 --> 49:13.492
Can I trust you on the taste?

49:13.575 --> 49:15.994
It's from a coffee shop
that Dam Ye-jin frequents,

49:16.078 --> 49:17.329
so it'll be good.

49:17.412 --> 49:19.373
-Dam Ye-jin?
-Yes.

49:19.456 --> 49:21.166
She was just at the coffee shop.

49:22.501 --> 49:24.419
Really? The coffee shop?

49:24.503 --> 49:27.172
Mr. Cha, you can head home now.

49:27.255 --> 49:30.008
The coffee smells so good
that I don't want to work late.

49:31.510 --> 49:33.970
You've been working so hard
without getting any rest.

49:34.054 --> 49:36.014
-Right.
-Get a lot of rest tonight.

49:36.098 --> 49:37.808
-I should get some sleep.
-And tomorrow…

49:37.891 --> 49:40.060
-Okay, all right. Go home now.
-With a relaxed mind…

49:40.143 --> 49:41.019
Go on. Good night!

49:41.103 --> 49:42.688
-Before bed…
-No, it's okay.

49:42.771 --> 49:44.690
-Good night!
-…massage your feet…

50:08.171 --> 50:09.506
What a coincidence.

50:11.133 --> 50:12.175
Mr. Seo.

50:12.676 --> 50:14.136
Did you come here for coffee?

50:14.219 --> 50:16.430
I came here to work.

50:17.472 --> 50:19.808
The espresso here is really good.

50:19.891 --> 50:20.892
I highly recommend it.

50:21.852 --> 50:23.061
I'll give it a try.

51:29.461 --> 51:31.880
Great. It's even raining.

51:58.949 --> 52:00.367
You don't have an umbrella?

52:01.076 --> 52:03.078
Then, should I save you this time?

52:14.881 --> 52:17.008
This is that umbrella, isn't it?

52:17.634 --> 52:18.677
Yes.

52:18.760 --> 52:21.555
It was the item that helped me
get my first-ever sellout.

52:22.806 --> 52:25.100
Try looking around when it rains.

52:25.183 --> 52:27.352
I bet at least one out of ten people
use this umbrella.

52:27.435 --> 52:28.728
Gosh, did you see that?

52:28.812 --> 52:30.230
At this point,

52:30.313 --> 52:32.774
I feel like I should ask you
for a nice meal sometime.

52:32.858 --> 52:34.359
Sure, when you're free--

52:34.442 --> 52:35.277
Tonight.

52:37.612 --> 52:39.281
Treat me to a meal tonight.

52:41.491 --> 52:42.659
What would you like?

52:45.120 --> 52:46.788
How about croissants?

52:50.625 --> 52:52.043
Mr. Seo…

52:54.379 --> 52:57.382
I don't date people I do business with.

52:58.425 --> 53:00.510
When my feelings got involved,

53:00.594 --> 53:03.388
I ended up losing
both my work and my relationship.

53:07.225 --> 53:08.059
All right.

53:09.227 --> 53:10.061
Let's work then.

53:11.354 --> 53:12.772
But once everything is resolved,

53:13.815 --> 53:16.860
let's have a nice meal together.

53:39.132 --> 53:41.343
I can't even hold my head up.

53:41.426 --> 53:43.845
You can just empty out my bag.

53:46.598 --> 53:48.016
OVERUSE IS STRICTLY PROHIBITED

54:06.159 --> 54:07.035
Thank you.

54:11.873 --> 54:14.000
Finally!

54:14.084 --> 54:15.794
You've been through so much, Rose.

54:15.877 --> 54:17.629
I'll treat you better from now on.

54:23.134 --> 54:24.052
Hello, Ms. Yang.

54:26.179 --> 54:27.097
Mr. Mechoori?

54:30.892 --> 54:32.018
What is it?

54:33.019 --> 54:34.187
My meds?

54:35.897 --> 54:38.233
You're right! I'll head over right now.

54:38.316 --> 54:40.485
It's late. Come tomorrow--

54:40.568 --> 54:42.112
No, I'll head over now.

54:42.195 --> 54:44.114
Do you know what time it is right now?

54:44.197 --> 54:45.991
It doesn't matter. Without my meds, I…

54:49.035 --> 54:50.245
All right.

54:50.328 --> 54:51.538
Then, let's meet halfway.

55:00.213 --> 55:02.799
Thank you. Have a good night.

55:04.259 --> 55:05.176
What's going on?

55:09.973 --> 55:12.183
Do you think

55:12.267 --> 55:15.603
I wouldn't notice those rocks
rattling around in your heart?

55:17.063 --> 55:17.981
Mechoori.

55:18.982 --> 55:22.819
Not even the harshest winter winds
can stop the spring breeze.

55:23.611 --> 55:26.114
You can't stop things
that force their way in

55:26.197 --> 55:27.574
no matter how hard you try.

55:27.657 --> 55:29.701
I'm sure you know that.

55:41.671 --> 55:43.506
HIT HOMESHOPPING

55:43.590 --> 55:45.967
SLEEP MEDICATION, SLEEP AID,
ANTI-ANXIETY MEDICATION

56:00.774 --> 56:01.649
Hello?

56:01.733 --> 56:03.068
Hey, Mechoori.

56:03.151 --> 56:05.403
There's an emergency.
Come to the farm right now!

56:09.866 --> 56:12.368
Mechoori, this is a disaster!

56:14.662 --> 56:15.663
What happened?

56:15.747 --> 56:17.707
I heard something, so I came to check,

56:17.791 --> 56:19.459
and this whole place was getting watered.

56:19.542 --> 56:21.878
There must've been an error
with the humidity controls.

56:21.961 --> 56:23.004
What do we do?

56:25.215 --> 56:26.966
We have to wash these quickly.

56:27.050 --> 56:28.802
It's only a matter of time
before they die.

56:29.302 --> 56:31.596
Let's fill
the high-pressure sprayer first.

56:33.515 --> 56:35.892
DEOKCHEON REST AREA

56:47.362 --> 56:48.988
I guess I got here first.

56:57.247 --> 56:58.123
TRASH

56:58.206 --> 56:59.499
I'm sorry.

57:30.071 --> 57:31.030
Where did it…

57:32.532 --> 57:33.616
Where is it?

57:36.703 --> 57:37.662
We have to save them.

57:45.420 --> 57:46.504
What do I do?

57:50.800 --> 57:52.719
Geez, I feel so stupid.

57:52.802 --> 57:53.887
I'm an idiot.

58:24.584 --> 58:25.418
Sung-mi.

58:27.378 --> 58:29.130
I can't pick up right now.

58:29.214 --> 58:31.341
MS. ANGRY EOM

58:34.802 --> 58:35.637
Geez.

58:52.487 --> 58:53.821
What's taking him so long?

59:32.777 --> 59:34.779
Mom said she'd come.

59:34.862 --> 59:36.656
She'll come soon.

59:42.954 --> 59:44.205
It's okay.

59:46.708 --> 59:47.542
It's okay.

59:52.297 --> 59:54.966
Mom said she'd come.

59:56.384 --> 59:58.136
She'll come soon.

59:58.219 --> 01:00:00.513
-It's okay.
-She'll come soon.

01:00:02.390 --> 01:00:03.891
She'll come soon.

01:00:10.440 --> 01:00:11.649
It's okay.

01:00:13.985 --> 01:00:14.986
It's okay.

01:00:16.779 --> 01:00:18.823
It's okay, Ye-jin.

01:00:19.991 --> 01:00:21.159
It's okay.

01:00:31.586 --> 01:00:32.670
Ms. Dam!

01:00:48.561 --> 01:00:49.479
I'm sorry.

01:02:20.820 --> 01:02:22.280
Earlier,

01:02:23.406 --> 01:02:24.741
well…

01:02:26.159 --> 01:02:27.577
it just ended up that way.

01:02:32.498 --> 01:02:33.416
I'm sorry I was late.

01:02:33.499 --> 01:02:34.333
Exactly.

01:02:35.042 --> 01:02:36.753
Do you have any idea what time it is?

01:02:36.836 --> 01:02:38.921
I was going to come right away, but--

01:02:39.005 --> 01:02:41.382
Forget it. Just give me my meds.

01:02:56.189 --> 01:02:57.356
Are you kidding me?

01:02:58.733 --> 01:02:59.859
I'll give you one each day.

01:03:02.904 --> 01:03:04.655
-What do you think you're doing?
-Ms. Dam.

01:03:08.034 --> 01:03:09.494
Let's meet every day.

01:03:15.750 --> 01:03:16.918
Mom.

01:03:18.002 --> 01:03:20.463
I went to a place called Deokpung Village.

01:03:21.756 --> 01:03:25.009
And I met someone really strange.

01:03:26.677 --> 01:03:28.679
He's so stubborn,

01:03:30.556 --> 01:03:35.186
and he keeps interrupting me when I talk.

01:03:38.147 --> 01:03:39.649
But the thing is…

01:03:41.943 --> 01:03:43.778
when I'm with him,

01:03:45.446 --> 01:03:47.198
I feel like

01:03:49.033 --> 01:03:51.035
everything's going to be okay.

01:03:54.455 --> 01:03:56.457
So…

01:03:58.125 --> 01:03:59.627
would it be okay

01:04:00.878 --> 01:04:02.797
to trust him instead of me…

01:04:05.091 --> 01:04:07.593
and try this again?

01:04:33.202 --> 01:04:37.331
Not even the harshest winter winds
can stop the spring breeze.

01:04:40.126 --> 01:04:42.879
You can't stop things
that force their way in

01:04:43.880 --> 01:04:45.381
no matter how hard you try.

01:04:54.807 --> 01:04:58.519
SOLD OUT ON YOU

01:05:28.883 --> 01:05:30.718
Were you with sweetie last night?

01:05:30.801 --> 01:05:33.679
I must be out of my mind. I must be crazy.

01:05:33.763 --> 01:05:35.139
Ms. Dam will contact you as well.

01:05:35.222 --> 01:05:37.350
Please tell me when she contacts you.

01:05:37.433 --> 01:05:39.352
Renewal? You're renewing the contract?

01:05:40.311 --> 01:05:41.270
Quit this right now.

01:05:41.354 --> 01:05:44.023
Ruining my life was enough,
don't you think?

01:05:45.191 --> 01:05:47.360
Would you ever consider
working for L'Étoile?

01:05:47.443 --> 01:05:51.656
Just think of this as giving Ms. Dam
a tour of this raw material farm.

01:05:51.739 --> 01:05:53.824
Today will be
the first and last shoot here.

01:05:53.908 --> 01:05:56.160
Then, why did you say yes
instead of refusing?

01:05:56.243 --> 01:05:57.828
It was because of you, Ms. Dam.

01:06:04.877 --> 01:06:06.879
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park
